															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/afx-neuromancer" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2739221); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2739221&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610223464" alt="AFX Neuromancer" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2739221)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/afx-neuromancer" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(2739221); return false;" >AFX Neuromancer</a></span> <span class="odate time_1549032206 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">01 Feb 2019 14:43</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4138114">
									

<p>I have a minor suggestion for the last sentence of the last paragraph of the containment procedures:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Weekly visits from a Level-3 approved psychiatrist have been scheduled on a weekly basis.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>The double-usage of the word &quot;weekly&quot; at the end is kind of redundant, and I would recommend trimming it to just read:</p>
<p>&quot;Weekly visits from a Level-3 approved psychiatrist have been scheduled.&quot;</p>
<p>The following bit seems to stem from the original article:</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;The&nbsp;building&nbsp;fronts&nbsp;are&nbsp;just&nbsp;fronts</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;For&nbsp;the&nbsp;people&nbsp;watching</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<blockquote>
<p>ceramic mask</p>
</blockquote>
<p>I don't think those masks were actually made of ceramic. I tried looking it up, but it's kind of hard to find (it's easy to find what the <em>rest</em> of the outfit was made from), but I think the mask was leather, too. I'm admittedly not certain about that. And apparently the outfit is anachronistic here, at least according to its self-proclaimed origin date, since it wasn't invented until the early 17th century.</p>
<p>Actually, now that I'm really looking at it, that mask in the picture doesn't even look like a legitimate plague doctor's mask. It looks like a Carnivale mask based off the plague doctors. I don't think it covers the lower half of his face, and the eyes should have glass lenses. I know this is one of the most iconic images on the site, I don't expect or even <em>want</em> it to be changed, just sayin'&#8230;</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p>Anyway, these two whopping issues are minor things and didn't stop me from enjoying this +1. Thank you for writing it!</p>

							</div>

								
					
