					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uncle-nicolini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3487700); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3487700&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610223464" alt="Uncle Nicolini" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3487700)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uncle-nicolini" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3487700); return false;" >Uncle Nicolini</a></span> <span class="odate time_1549045281 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">01 Feb 2019 18:21</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4138371">
									

<p>Hey, thank you for reading and offering feedback! My responses are below. :)</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Anesthesia- That is not something I'm 100% on, but it's a rule of the canon. According to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/captain-kirby" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3440103); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3440103&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1549045499" alt="Captain Kirby" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3440103)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/captain-kirby" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3440103); return false;">Captain Kirby</a></span>, anesthesia no longer works because&#8230; I don't know why. I wish I could give you a reason but I simply don't have one. I know a tale in EoD from S1 mentions this but I can't recall it by name at the moment.</p>
<p>I suppose even if local anesthesia did work, 049 would likely just do it on his own anyway out of pride.</p>
<p>&#8212;BP Disorder- I used some of my old college literature (which may or may not be out of date now, now that I give it some thought!) to frame his diagnosis. Here are the symptoms I picked out.</p>
<ul>
<li>Chronic feelings of emptiness.</li>
<li>Unclear or shifting self-image</li>
<li>Anxiety</li>
</ul>
<p>I've been told a few times that Bipolar Disorder fits better, and I'm contemplating changing it to this unless I find something better.&#8212;</p>
<p>I've changed it to Bipolar Personality Disorder based on your suggestions. Thank you! :D</p>
<p>Surgery- Even in a post-death world, people still get shot, tumors occur, and augments need to be installed. You're right, it's pretty kid-glovey, but that's really the best they can do given the situation. I am open to suggestion. :D</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

