			<div class="content" id="post-content-4138405">
									

<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Fair enough on the canon anesthesia thing, I didn't know it was a replicated mistake.</p>
<blockquote>
<ul>
<li>Chronic feelings of emptiness.</li>
<li>Unclear or shifting self-image</li>
<li>Anxiety</li>
</ul>
</blockquote>
<p>There's 50% of the population (lol). These are symptoms of Borderline/Bipolar, sure, but they are non-specific; like trying to propose a diagnosis for something based on headaches and fatigue. Could be a million things, all of which would include headaches and fatigue in the symptoms list. I'm not faulting you for this, just offering some expertise.</p>
<p>In my unbidden opinion, I'd say bipolar would be better, but still not accurate. Bipolars go through manic phases where they feel like they are, well, manic &#8212; on top of the world. They cycle between this and deep depressions where they will just shut down for days. I suppose we could be seeing the depressive phase of a bipolar 049 here, but we'd expect a serious and amphetamine-like 180° at some point for the diagnosis to stand. If I were consulted, I'd say it is just depressive disorder or generalized anxiety disorder.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>Even in a post-death world, people still get shot, tumors occur, and augments need to be installed.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>What I was getting at is that most surgical procedures, those following these injuries too, would be to prevent death or other serious sequelae. I'm not sure how much justification most procedures would carry in this world, especially given real world considerations of expense. You 're right; I think augmentation would remain.</p>
<p>As for the delicate handling of 049; I don't know what the answer is, but it's my main gripe. Feels like the tale has equivocated how the Foundation in-universe would approach 049 and how the community would want a classic character treated .</p>
</div>
</div>
